Estimate tree

result <- crtree(
  demo, 
  rvar = "response", 
  evar = c("female", "income", "age"), 
  type = "classification", 
  lev = "yes", 
  cp = -1, 
  K = 4,
  data_filter = "training == 1"
)
plot(result, plots = "prune", custom = FALSE)

plot(result, orient = "TD", width = "900px") %>% render()

The pruning plot suggests 3 nodes is the best solution …

result <- crtree(
  demo, 
  rvar = "response", 
  evar = c("female", "income", "age"), 
  type = "classification", 
  lev = "yes", 
  cp = -1, 
  nodes = 3,
  data_filter = "training == 1"
)
summary(result, prn = TRUE)
